<td>$22.7bn</td>
<td>137,000</td>
<td>2008</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>This group was once known as the "Big Eight", and was reduced to the "Big Five" by a series of <a href="/wiki/Merger" title="Merger" class="mw-redirect">mergers</a>. The Big Five became the Big Four after the near-demise of <a href="/wiki/Arthur_Andersen" title="Arthur Andersen">Arthur Andersen</a> in 2002, following its involvement in the <a href="/wiki/Enron_scandal" title="Enron scandal">Enron Scandal</a>.</p>
